just_use auto_player.py

# label: EARLY (auto-player)
# role: agent tool — plays a full LynRummy session end-to-end via /hint

Walks the /hint suggestions list and takes the FIRST one each
turn, posting its action verbatim. When no hints fire, calls
complete_turn and classifies the result. Exits on
success_as_victor / success_with_hand_emptied, or after
max-actions.

Not an optimizer. Not "greedy." Mirrors a human playing the most
obvious trick — which is the /hint endpoint's native contract
(priority-ranked, simplest first).

## Surface

- `python3 tools/lynrummy_elm_player/auto_player.py` — fresh session.
- `--session N` — resume an existing session (useful when Steve
  creates a two-player game from the Elm UI and Claude joins as
  the other seat).
- `--max-actions N` — safety cap (default 200).

## Pointers

- Depends on: `client.py` (same dir), `/hint` + `/actions` + `/score`
  endpoints in `views/lynrummy_elm.go`.
- Replaces: the deleted `greedy.py` (commit ffb7a6a then bcaea72
  rip). Score-maximizing was pivoted out when the hint system
  simplified to priority-ordered suggestions.
